<h4 id="2-4-7-focus-visible-aa"><a href="https://www.w3.org/TR/UNDERSTANDING-WCAG20/navigation-mechanisms-focus-visible.html">2.4.7 Focus visible (AA)</a></h4>
<p>It must be easy to tell which element has keyboard focus. This helps sighted keyboard users orient themselves within the page, and confidently interact with it.</p>
<h5 id="requirements-what-to-do">Requirements / What to do?</h5>
<ul>
<li>  Interactive elements like links, buttons, and form fields, have a visible focus indicator.</li>
</ul>
<h5 id="common-mistakes">Common mistakes</h5>
<ul>
<li>  The browser default focus indicator has not been replaced with something that is easier to see;</li>
<li>  An indicator has been provided for mouse hover, but not duplicated for keyboard focus.</li>
</ul>
